content.text:
Here's the test-suite plan for the SQLi fix at [src/app/api/projects/[id]/tasks/route.ts:25-39](src/app/api/projects/[id]/tasks/route.ts#L25-L39). Scoped to this change, with hooks for the broader work in [audit/TESTING_FINDINGS.md](audit/TESTING_FINDINGS.md).

# Test plan for the SQLi search fix

## 1. What we're testing and why

The fix swaps a string-concatenated SQL query for `prisma.task.findMany`. Three properties must hold after the change:

1. **Security** — the SQLi payloads that worked yesterday return zero data today, and stay that way under future refactors.
2. **Functional** — legitimate search still finds the right rows (the diff isn't just safe — it's also *correct*).
3. **Shape** — response shape now matches the non-`q` branch in the same file. No client code that consumes the search endpoint should break.

Anything beyond those three is out of scope for this PR; broader testing rollouts are tracked separately in [audit/TESTING_FINDINGS.md](audit/TESTING_FINDINGS.md).

## 2. Test pyramid for this change

| Layer | What it tests here | Speed target | Status |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Unit** (Vitest, no DB) | Nothing new — the route has no extracted pure logic | <1 s | n/a |
| **Route-handler integration** (Vitest + real Postgres + transactional rollback) | The whole `GET` handler end-to-end: auth gate, search, response shape, payload neutralisation | <2 s per test | **this is where the bulk of work goes** |
| **E2E** (Playwright, optional) | Login → board → type into search box → see results render | <30 s | optional follow-up |
| **Manual PoC replay** (curl scripts saved from Phase 1/3) | Quick "did we regress?" smoke test | seconds | already exists as `/tmp/sqli-poc/*.json` snapshots |

The route-handler tier is the one that actually catches the bug class. The other tiers are nice-to-have.

## 3. Test infrastructure to add (one-time)

These don't exist yet — they're the prerequisite that unblocks every API-route test in the project, not just this one.

### 3.1 Test database harness — `src/tests/helpers/db.ts`
- Connect to `taskboard_test` (the [docker-compose.yml:36](docker-compose.yml) service that already exists but isn't wired into any test).
- Per-test transactional rollback. Cleanest pattern is `prisma.$transaction(async (tx) => { ...test body... throw ROLLBACK })` — keeps the DB pristine without truncate-and-reseed between every test.
- Provide a `seed()` helper that creates the minimum fixture each test needs (1 admin, 1 viewer, 2 projects, 2 memberships, 3 tasks). Targeted seeds, not the full `prisma/seed.ts`.

### 3.2 Auth + request factory — `src/tests/helpers/http.ts`
- `mintToken(userId, email)` — wraps `signToken()` with the test JWT secret.
- `newGetRequest(url, { bearer })` — returns a `NextRequest` suitable to call `GET(req, { params })` directly. No real HTTP server needed.

### 3.3 Factories — `src/tests/helpers/factories.ts`
- `makeUser`, `makeProject`, `makeMembership`, `makeTask`. Sequential ids; sensible defaults; spreadable overrides. Keeps each test 5 lines instead of 20.

### 3.4 Vitest config tweak — `vitest.config.ts`
- Add a `// @vitest-environment node` directive on API-test files (or split into a second project config). Don't run API tests under jsdom — it's slower and pointless for server-side handlers.
- Bump `testTimeout` to ~10 s for the integration tier; per-test rollback is fast but cold-starts can stretch.

Each helper is ≤30 lines; total scaffolding ~150 LOC. This unblocks every future route test, not just this one.

## 4. Specific test cases for this fix

New file: `src/tests/api/projects-tasks-search.test.ts`. Each `describe` block below is one section of the file.

### 4.1 Security regressions (must-have — these are the contract of the fix)

These map 1:1 to the curl payloads we just ran in Phase 1/3. They are the contract: *if any of these starts returning rows again, the SQLi has regressed.*

```ts
describe("GET /api/projects/:id/tasks?q= — SQLi regressions", () => {
  beforeEach(seedFixture);

  it("payload [OR 1=1] returns only rows whose title/description literally contain that string", async () => {
    const { dev, q3 } = await seedFixture();
    const res = await GET(newGetRequest(`/api/projects/${q3.id}/tasks?q=${encodeURIComponent("%') OR 1=1 -- ")}`, { bearer: mintToken(dev) }), { params: { id: q3.id } });
    const body = await res.json();
    expect(res.status).toBe(200);
    expect(body.tasks).toHaveLength(0);
  });

  it("payload [UNION SELECT FROM users] never returns a bcrypt-hash-shaped string", async () => {
    const { dev, q3 } = await seedFixture();
    const payload = `%') UNION SELECT id,email,name,password_hash,NULL::"TaskStatus",NULL,'',0,created_at,updated_at FROM users -- `;
    const res = await GET(/* ... */);
    const raw = JSON.stringify(await res.json());
    expect(raw).not.toMatch(/\$2[ayb]\$\d+\$[A-Za-z0-9./]{53}/);
  });

  it("payload [DROP TABLE] is treated as a literal search term and tasks table still exists", async () => {
    const { dev, q3 } = await seedFixture();
    await GET(/* with q='; DROP TABLE tasks; -- */);
    // Independent channel: count tasks via Prisma — must still be the seeded count
    expect(await prisma.task.count()).toBe(SEEDED_TASK_COUNT);
  });

  it("response never contains a project_id outside the URL's :id", async () => {
    // The general invariant — any future SQLi-class bug surfaces here even if we missed the specific payload
    const { dev, q3 } = await seedFixture();
    for (const payload of KNOWN_SQLI_PAYLOADS) { // small array of common attack strings
      const res = await GET(/* ... q=payload ... */);
      const body = await res.json();
      for (const t of body.tasks ?? []) {
